The paper discusses the designing of architectures for deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and systems and control (cs.SY). However, since the paper focuses on the neural architecture search (NAS) methods, which are primarily used in deep learning, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, followed by cs.CV and cs.AI. The sub-categories of cs.NE and cs.SY are less likely but still relevant due to the discussion of neural networks and system design.
